text.__SUMMARY__: Conasprella traversiana is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails and their allies.
text.Description: The size of the shell varies between 19 mm and 43 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species occurs off Aden and Somalia
text.References:
Smith, E. A. 1875. Description of a new species of Conus. Quarterly Journal of Conchology 1:107-108, 1 fig.
Puillandre N., Duda T.F., Meyer C., Olivera B.M. & Bouchet P. (2015). One, four or 100 genera? A new classification of the cone snails. Journal of Molluscan Studies. 81: 1-23
